Package entity

Class CountryEntity

java.lang.Object
entity.CountryEntity
@Entity public class CountryEntity extends Object
Entity class representing a Country in the database. This class is mapped to the table "country" and contains details about a country's name, money, population, and associated resource nodes.

  • Field Details

    • id

      private Long id
      Primary key of the "country" table. The ID is auto-generated using the IDENTITY strategy.

    • name

      private String name
      Name of the country. This field is unique and cannot be null.

    • money

      private double money
      The amount of money available to the country. This field cannot be null.

    • population

      private Long population
      The population of the country. This field cannot be null.

    • resourceNodes

      private Set<ResourceNodeEntity> resourceNodes
      A collection of resource nodes associated with this country. Defines a one-to-many relationship with ResourceNodeEntity. The "country" field in ResourceNodeEntity is the mapped column. Any changes to this collection will cascade to the related entities.
